HEADWORD: Indomitable
<hw>In*dom"i*ta*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indomitabilis</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> not +
<ets>domitare</ets>, intens. fr. <ets>domare</ets> to tame. See
<er>Tame</er>.]</ety> <def>Not to be subdued; untamable; invincible;
<as>as, an <ex>indomitable</ex> will, courage, animal</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

